JETHSUR SURANGBHAI V. STATE OF GUJARAT [1983] INSC 174; AIR 1984 SC 151; 1984 (1) SCR 797; 1983 (2) SCALE 709 (9 November 1983)

 FAZALALI, SYED MURTAZA FAZALALI, SYED MURTAZA MISRA, R.B. (J) THAKKAR, M.P. (J) 
CITATION: 1984 AIR 151 1984 SCR (1) 797 1983 SCALE (2)709 
ACT:
 Indian Penal Code 1860, Ss. 120 B, 109, 408, 467 and 471.
 Chairman of Co-operative Society along with others charged with conspiracy to commit criminal breach of trust- Charge of conspiracy having failed-Sessions Court acquitting all but one accused-Appeal by State-High Court convicting Chairman-Conviction whether valid and legal.
 Defalcation of properties-Several accused charged with conspiracy-Prosecution to prove collusion and cohesion among all accused-Mens rea not to be excluded-If charge of conspiracy fails-Prosecution to prove affirmatively that accused directly and personally connected with acts or omissions.
 
